By: Rainer Maria Rilke
Source:
  ID: 631057a1-0221-4885-ba61-78b661b62b70
  Locus:
    Daily: April 2
  Source:
    Description: December 5, 1914
    Title: Letter to Marianne von Goldschmidt-Rothschild
Title: To Make Sense of Things
---
I yearn for my work, because it always helps me make sense of things.
For never was a horror experienced without an angel stepping in from
the opposite direction to witness it with me.
